# Troubleshooting Guide
Common Errors
Error 1: NULL customer_id
Symptom: Pipeline fails at Silver layer
Error Message: Constraint violation: valid_customer Row with NULL customer_id found
Solution Options:
Option 1 - Filter out NULLs: .filter(col("customer_id").isNotNull())
Option 2 - Change validation rule: @dlt.expect_or_drop("valid_customer", "customer_id IS NOT NULL")
Option 3 - Investigate source: Check why source system sends NULL customer_ids
Error 2: Negative Amount
Symptom: Pipeline fails data quality check
Error Message: Constraint violation: valid_amount Negative amount detected: -50.00
Solution Options:
Option 1 - Filter negative amounts: .filter(col("amount") > 0)
Option 2 - Handle refunds separately: .withColumn("amount", abs(col("amount")))
Option 3 - Create refunds table: Separate positive orders from refunds
Error 3: Invalid Date Format
Symptom: Pipeline fails during date parsing
Error Message: Cannot parse 'invalid-date' as DATE
Solution:
Use safe date parsing: .withColumn("order_date", to_date(col("order_date"), "yyyy-MM-dd")) .filter(col("order_date").isNotNull())
Handles invalid dates gracefully by converting to NULL then filtering.
Troubleshooting Workflow
1. Check Error Log Table:    SELECT * FROM retail_demo.monitoring.error_log ORDER BY timestamp DESC
2. Identify Failed Layer:    Look at 'layer' column (bronze/silver/gold)
3. Find Error Type:    Check 'error_type' and 'error_message'
4. Apply Solution:    Use recommended solution from 'solution' column
5. Test Fix:    Re-run pipeline and verify
6. Update Status:    Mark error as 'resolved' in error_log table
